Weâ€™re excited to share more about how our collaboration with Cert Center Canada and the University of Toronto is shaping the future of advanced air mobility. 
 
The project is focused on developing an all-weather lift system for next-generation vertical takeoff aircraft. 
 
Many current platforms, including traditional helicopters, face limitations in icing conditions, where critical systems like rotors and exposed components are vulnerable to ice buildup. 
 
Our Cavorite X7 tackles this challenge head-on. Its closing wing design keeps vital systems protected from the elements and simplifies de-icing, reducing downtime and improving operational safety.
